### Custom Attributes

Declare within a Constraint tag using the <CustomAttribute\> tag

Only has 2 real tags: the attribute name (via attributeName) and the value (via the custom<Type>Value attribute)

- Uses reflection for setName, similar to ObjectAnimator

- Needs the attributeName tag with the name of the desired attribute to change (backgroundColor, alpha, etc) e.x. motion:attributeName=“backgroundColor”

- Possible value tags:
    - customColorValue
    - customIntegerValue
    - customFloatValue
    - customStringValue
    - customDimension
    - customBoolean
    
- Both start and end constraints must define the same custom attribute (e.x can’t define backgroundColor in the start but not the end)